      <img src="screens/sc9.jpeg"  alt="Screenshot 9"  class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg">
      <img src="screens/sc10.jpeg" alt="Screenshot 10" class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg">
      <img src="screens/sc11.png"  alt="Screenshot 11" class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg">
      <img src="screens/sc12.jpeg" alt="Screenshot 12" class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg">
      <img src="screens/sc13.png"  alt="Screenshot 13" class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg">
      <img src="screens/sc14.png"  alt="Screenshot 14" class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg">
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── TESTIMONIALS ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="s4-testimonials">
    <div class="s4-t-inner">

      <div class="s4-t-header">
        <div>
          <span class="s4-t-eyebrow">What people say</span>
          <h2 class="s4-t-title">We love our users.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="s4-t-sub">User happiness is our primary target. If our community isn't happy, we're not succeeding.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="s4-t-grid">

        <div class="s4-t-card">
          <p class="s4-t-quote">It's a lightweight OS free of bloat with modest hardware requirements, but still manages to contain everything an average user might need.</p>
          <div class="s4-t-footer">
            <img class="s4-t-avatar" src="icons/jason.jpg" alt="Jason Evangelho" />
            <div class="s4-t-person">
              <span class="s4-t-name">Jason Evangelho</span>
              <span class="s4-t-role">Contributor at Forbes</span>
            </div>
            <span class="s4-t-pub">Forbes</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="s4-t-card">
          <p class="s4-t-quote">It provides all the benefits of Ubuntu and its ecosystem, but feathered beneath a clean, modern looking desktop interface.</p>
          <div class="s4-t-footer">
            <img class="s4-t-avatar" src="icons/joey.jpg" alt="Joey Sneddon" />
            <div class="s4-t-person">
              <span class="s4-t-name">Joey Sneddon</span>
              <span class="s4-t-role">Editor at OMG! Ubuntu</span>
            </div>
            <span class="s4-t-pub">OMG! Ubuntu</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="s4-t-card">
          <p class="s4-t-quote">After the GNOME-based version, the biggest changes to an Ubuntu flavor come in Ubuntu Budgie.</p>
          <div class="s4-t-footer">
            <img class="s4-t-avatar" src="icons/scott.jpg" alt="Scott Gilbertson" />
            <div class="s4-t-person">
              <span class="s4-t-name">Scott Gilbertson</span>
              <span class="s4-t-role">Editor at Ars Technica</span>
            </div>
            <span class="s4-t-pub">Ars Technica</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="s4-t-card">
          <p class="s4-t-quote">The Perfect Blend of Ubuntu and Budgie Desktop. Ubuntu Budgie provides a superior computing experience.</p>
          <div class="s4-t-footer">
            <img class="s4-t-avatar" src="icons/aquil.jpg" alt="Aquil Roshan" />
            <div class="s4-t-person">
              <span class="s4-t-name">Aquil Roshan</span>
              <span class="s4-t-role">Writer at ItsFoss</span>
            </div>
            <span class="s4-t-pub">ItsFoss</span>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── SPONSORS ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="s4-sponsors">
